44817430892618", "author": "warmax356", "author_handle": "warmax356", "user_id": "347456552023752717", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/347456552023752717/b1aff00182ced46cfad988ad2bf53d3f.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Wednesday, January 7, 2026 1:21 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-01-07 1:21 a.m.", "text": "So an update, my seed studio solar nodes arrived and will replace my heltec v2 as a repeater - since i started this journey only ping i got was from @Dayle - M0OUE but on another firmwire on other devices since publishing about both on my open source community blog the other firmwires took much more adoption Still learning on these platforms and wondering if i should use both on 868 or switch meshcore to 433 to establish the more common link to sicily according to the map and build on that leaving 868 for the other firmwire and avoid cross talk, though 433 is heavily used by remote controlled doors.gates and other devices", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>So an update, my seed studio solar nodes arrived and will replace my heltec v2 as a repeater - since i started this journey only ping i got was from <span class=\"chatlog__markdown-mention\" title=\"atomic_zombie\">@Dayle - M0OUE</span>  but on another firmwire on other devices  since publishing about both on my open source community blog the other firmwires took much more adoption\n\nStill learning on these platforms and wondering if i should use both on 868 or switch meshcore to 433 to establish the more common link to sicily according to the map and build on that leaving 868 for the other firmwire and avoid cross talk, though 433 is heavily used by remote controlled doors.gates and other devices</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "<div class=chatlog__reactions><div class=chatlog__reaction title=thumbsup><img class=\"chatlog__emoji chatlog__emoji--small\" alt=👍 src=https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f44d.svg loading=lazy> <span class=chatlog__reaction-count>1</span></div></div>", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1458585293232799898", "author": "warmax356", "author_handle": "warmax356", "user_id": "347456552023752717", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/347456552023752717/b1aff00182ced46cfad988ad2bf53d3f.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Wednesday, January 7, 2026 5:17 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-01-07 5:17 p.m.", "text": "Thanks dayle yes they have the same issue on meshtastic with medium-fast rather than long-fast but got a mate there that might do the bridge using thier mqtt or the jumper pin method (edited)", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Thanks dayle yes they have the same issue on meshtastic with medium-fast rather than long-fast but got a mate there that might do the bridge using thier mqtt or the jumper pin method</span> <span class=chatlog__edited-timestamp title=\"Wednesday, January 7, 2026 6:06 p.m.\">(edited)</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}]}